1
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:12,190
Gai.

2
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:14,810
I-I've parked the car at the company.

3
00:00:15,190 --> 00:00:15,920
Don't worry.

4
00:00:18,070 --> 00:00:19,280
Be careful with it!

5
00:00:20,810 --> 00:00:21,410
Gai, it was nothing.

6
00:00:21,410 --> 00:00:23,270
J-Just a sound-activated light.

7
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:26,110
Okay.

8
00:00:26,920 --> 00:00:27,430
Gai.

9
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:28,820
Alright, alright.

10
00:00:29,030 --> 00:00:30,630
Call me if you need anything.

11
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,160
Alright, Gai.

12
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:35,030
Alright.

13
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:48,970
You must get it fixed

14
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,840
before tonight.

15
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:53,130
Bro.

16
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:54,790
Your bumper's completely broken.

17
00:00:54,790 --> 00:00:56,030
I'll have to replace it with a new one.

18
00:00:56,030 --> 00:00:57,030
Replace it then!

19
00:00:58,280 --> 00:00:59,240
Anyway, before tonight,

20
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:00,860
you have to get it fixed.

21
00:01:01,030 --> 00:01:01,600
Alright?

22
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,840
I'll go get the money for you right away.

23
00:01:19,430 --> 00:01:20,140
Daddy.

24
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:44,620
[Born with Luck]

25
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:47,610
[Episode 17]

26
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:49,970
What are you doing!

27
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,850
Trying to hit me, huh?

28
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:54,240
What are you thinking?

29
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,190
Trying to escape?

30
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:56,400
My people are all over this place.

31
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,260
Don't even think about escaping!

32
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,320
Chao.

33
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:04,870
This God of Wealth statue

34
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:05,800
looks like ours.

35
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:08,740
You know what, it really does.

36
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,120
Where did

37
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:12,050
you two pop out from?

38
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:12,680
Shut up.

39
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:16,070
We're robbers.

40
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,430
Robbers?

41
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:19,410
The two of you?

42
00:03:20,430 --> 00:03:22,240
You don't even know who I am, do you?

43
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,230
Shut up.

44
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,970
Now, can the two of us

45
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,300
rob you or not?

46
00:03:28,079 --> 00:03:29,190
Can we or not?

47
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:30,530
Sorry.

48
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:32,770
I was just kidding.

49
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:34,910
Someone!

50
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,040
Is that Rong's voice?

51
00:03:41,780 --> 00:03:43,650
Yeah. That's pretty loud.

52
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:47,590
There's no one else here.

53
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,960
Didn't we see all his men leave

54
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,190
when we came in?

55
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:00,750
Wait. You want money, right?

56
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:01,880
I've got money here.

57
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:03,750
This—

58
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:05,950
all yours.

59
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,060
Take it all.

60
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:07,900
Don't move.

61
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:09,710
Just this little?

62
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,840
I-I don't keep

63
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:14,530
cash at home.

64
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:15,870
Don't you usually brag

65
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:17,930
that your house is loaded with money?

66
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,360
Wh...

67
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:21,120
When did I ever say that?

68
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:22,380
You're asking me when?

69
00:04:24,540 --> 00:04:25,870
Can I transfer it to you?

70
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,570
Do you think we're so stupid

71
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,260
as to take a bank transfer?

72
00:04:29,430 --> 00:04:31,260
Then that's all the cash I have.

73
00:04:31,390 --> 00:04:32,120
I hate people

74
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:33,880
who are full of hot air the most.

75
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:37,210
We only got this little bit in the end?

76
00:04:41,270 --> 00:04:41,850
Don't!

77
00:04:44,510 --> 00:04:46,310
There's money in that suitcase.

78
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,270
You can take all the money
in that suitcase.

79
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:50,930
Let me keep my phone, will you?

80
00:04:51,170 --> 00:04:52,130
There are...

81
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:55,290
There are photos of
a deceased relative of mine on it.

82
00:04:59,190 --> 00:04:59,720
Is it him?

83
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:24,760
Is this the money you talked about?

84
00:05:36,810 --> 00:05:37,700
One million.

85
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,380
US dollars.

86
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:42,580
Let me keep some memories, okay?

87
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,210
You can take all the money.

88
00:05:46,510 --> 00:05:47,360
But please,

89
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,930
let me keep my phone.

90
00:05:51,190 --> 00:05:53,770
♪ Bunny, bunny, bunny, bunny,
bunny, bunny ♪

91
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,380
You're a sentimental guy.

92
00:05:54,700 --> 00:05:55,960
♪ Love you, love you, love you ♪

93
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,290
It's just a shabby phone anyway.
Here you are.

94
00:05:57,450 --> 00:06:00,000
♪ Bunny, bunny, bunny, bunny,
bunny, bunny ♪

95
00:06:00,270 --> 00:06:01,310
Thank you.

96
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:01,210
♪ Love you ♪

97
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:04,110
That's not right.

98
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:06,280
You are lying to us.

99
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:06,630
No.

100
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:08,270
It's just a shabby phone.

101
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:11,530
Password.

102
00:06:12,430 --> 00:06:13,960
Let me see the other photos.

103
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,100
I have no idea.

104
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,630
You don't know the password
to your own phone?

105
00:06:17,630 --> 00:06:18,800
How can you not know?

106
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:20,920
Chao.

107
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:22,460
He saw my face.

108
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:23,310
I didn't.

109
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:24,990
This is not over.

110
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:27,040
Spare him. He's still useful.

111
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:27,560
Useful.

112
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:31,970
Do you have a business card?

113
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,659
[Zhou Rong, Chairman]

114
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,159
Mr. Zhou, if you call the police

115
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:41,120
after you wake up,

116
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:41,920
then this phone will...

117
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:42,870
I absolutely won't.

118
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:43,870
Never come back.

119
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:44,870
I won't.

120
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:47,040
Our main job today

121
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:48,020
is robbery.

122
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:49,680
As for business matters,

123
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:51,140
we can discuss them later.

124
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:53,320
We'll contact you when you wake up.

125
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:55,330
What do you mean "wake up"?

126
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,240
What do you want to do?

127
00:07:00,870 --> 00:07:01,600
It hurts.

128
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,250
Chief Zhang, what should we do?

129
00:07:37,940 --> 00:07:38,870
You go in with me.

130
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:39,920
The rest of you, wait here.

131
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,390
Yes.

132
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:43,650
W-Who are you looking for?

133
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,560
I'm the Deputy Chief

134
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,480
of Sanjiangkou Public Security Bureau,

135
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,280
Zhang Yi'ang.

136
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:48,650
I want to see Zhou Rong.

137
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,409
Please wait here for a moment.

138
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:42,780
Stop there.

139
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:46,750
Stop right there!

140
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:53,040
I need to see Mr. Zhou about something.

141
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:03,240
She's a police officer.

142
00:09:04,630 --> 00:09:05,560
Go check on Rong.

143
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:21,750
Put it down!

144
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:23,240
Police.

145
00:09:25,270 --> 00:09:26,000
Officers,

146
00:09:26,390 --> 00:09:27,080
she's a thief!

147
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:29,280
-I was trying to catch a thief.
-Enough.

148
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,790
She's also a police officer.

149
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:33,250
What were you trying to do
in broad daylight?

150
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:36,600
Does being police mean you can just
trespass into a private residence?

151
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,240
I should ask you what you want to do

152
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:39,100
in broad daylight instead, okay?

153
00:09:43,270 --> 00:09:43,750
Chief.

154
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:45,480
Zhou Rong was robbed

155
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,080
by two masked men.

156
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:46,810
In the study.

157
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,360
Did you hear that?

158
00:09:50,390 --> 00:09:50,890
He was rob...

159
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:52,140
There was a robbery.

160
00:09:52,390 --> 00:09:53,440
This is a crime scene.

161
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,910
We're going to
conduct an investigation now.

162
00:09:54,910 --> 00:09:56,200
No, no need to investigate.

163
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,480
No need to investigate.

164
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,410
Chief Zhang.

165
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,550
I was just having a drink

166
00:10:00,550 --> 00:10:01,600
with 2 friends over there.

167
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,000
So,

168
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,320
there was no robbery.

169
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,240
Did you hear that?

170
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,360
There was no robbery.

171
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:07,790
Since there was no robbery,
then you're trespassing.

172
00:10:07,790 --> 00:10:09,590
I'm acting in self-defense now!

173
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,200
Didn't you just say

174
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,040
I was a thief?

175
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:14,240
If the police are catching a thief,

176
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,640
how is that trespassing?

177
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,390
Chief, hurry to the study.

178
00:10:17,390 --> 00:10:18,150
N-No need.

179
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:19,600
You're...

180
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:23,820
You're also

181
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,400
a guest I invited, right?

182
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:27,760
Chief Zhang.

183
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,050
Everyone here today

184
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:30,050
was invited by me.

185
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,360
Everything in my house is peaceful

186
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,270
and perfectly fine today.

187
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:32,840
Really.

188
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:34,680
Put the sticks down.

189
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:39,750
He really was robbed.

190
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,210
A whole suitcase of money.

191
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:42,750
Mr. Zhou,

192
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,360
tell us if you lost anything.

193
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,510
We will help you get it back.

194
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:46,080
I didn't.

195
00:10:46,630 --> 00:10:47,120
You see, Chief Zhang,

196
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:48,000
with you in charge of Sanjiangkou,

197
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,240
who would dare to commit a robbery?

198
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:50,200
Who would dare to rob

199
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,840
a suitcase of money from someone's study
in broad daylight, right?

200
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,370
Besides,

201
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:53,080
how could there be

202
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,670
a suitcase of money in a study, right?

203
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:55,630
Also, look around—

204
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:57,090
it's like a fortress here.

205
00:11:04,910 --> 00:11:05,710
So, no losses?

206
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:07,880
Really none?

207
00:11:10,790 --> 00:11:12,050
Did you lose anything?

208
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:13,790
Did you lose anything?

209
00:11:13,790 --> 00:11:14,590
Did you or not?

210
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,550
No, no. I didn't.

211
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,460
Did you lose anything?

212
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:28,080
No.

213
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,510
How did they get in?

214
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:45,190
Mr. Zhou.

215
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:47,080
The police entering
doesn't count as trespassing.

216
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,150
They wanted to see you.

217
00:11:48,150 --> 00:11:49,240
I called you but you didn't answer,

218
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,370
so I brought them in.

219
00:11:53,670 --> 00:11:54,000
Rong...

220
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:54,720
Shut up!

221
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:56,240
I was in there yelling for someone
for ages!

222
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:57,440
How come nobody came?

223
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,870
Is my house somewhere

224
00:11:58,870 --> 00:12:00,330
anyone can just walk into?

225
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:03,050
Is this how you guard the house?

226
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,000
Aren't you dizzy?

227
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:08,360
Yes.

228
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:09,840
I am.

229
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,330
Then fall down already!

230
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,150
Aren't you dizzy? Aren't you?

231
00:12:21,150 --> 00:12:21,840
Aren't you?

232
00:12:36,870 --> 00:12:37,670
Chief,

233
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,240
I really didn't go undercover on my own

234
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,440
without permission.

235
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:41,750
No one's blaming you.

236
00:12:42,550 --> 00:12:43,810
Tell us what happened.

237
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:45,080
Mr. Zhou.

238
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:46,250
Please.

239
00:12:50,790 --> 00:12:51,790
I tried to escape,

240
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:53,440
but there were people outside.

241
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,750
I heard Zhu Yifei

242
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:56,850
and Zhou Rong trading the bianzhong.

243
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:59,210
Keep your eyes on the road.

244
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:01,080
Trading the bianzhong?

245
00:13:02,390 --> 00:13:03,090
And then?

246
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,510
Then I sneaked out, trying to escape,

247
00:13:04,510 --> 00:13:06,480
but bumped into Zhou Rong
as soon as I got out.

248
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:08,340
So I had to follow him to the study.

249
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:11,300
Then two armed men in maid outfits

250
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:13,270
with their faces covered showed up.

251
00:13:13,270 --> 00:13:14,400
In women's clothes?

252
00:13:14,510 --> 00:13:15,670
-Female...
-Male...

253
00:13:15,670 --> 00:13:16,550
-Male.
-Male.

254
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:19,770
They knocked me out,

255
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,910
took Zhou Rong's 1 million US dollars,

256
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:23,120
as well as a phone that was

257
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,320
very important to him.

258
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:24,960
The wallpaper

259
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,360
was a photo of Lang Bowen.

260
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:28,450
Then they ran away.

261
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:30,200
Then I woke up.

262
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:31,930
And then, you arrived.

263
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:32,840
You already saw it,

264
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,360
so how could you let them

265
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:34,490
take the phone away?

266
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,800
I was a bit dizzy then.

267
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:39,030
B-Being dizzy is no excuse.

268
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:40,030
That phone is definitely

269
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:41,000
a very important clue.

270
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,060
Look at you. You...

271
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:43,270
They were

272
00:13:44,030 --> 00:13:45,090
2 armed fugitives.

273
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:46,750
You can't expect her to confront them

274
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:48,950
empty-handed and risk her life, right?

275
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,270
It's important to protect yourself.

276
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:53,930
You didn't do anything wrong.

277
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:10,510
R-Rong.

278
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,670
Why are you back so late?

279
00:14:13,670 --> 00:14:15,000
I took our men
and chased them all the way,

280
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:15,670
almost out of the city,

281
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:17,120
but we didn't see Zhu Yifei
and the others.

282
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,320
Then halfway through,

283
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,960
I got a call saying

284
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:20,720
something had happened at home,

285
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,910
so I rushed back immediately.

286
00:14:21,910 --> 00:14:22,870
Where's my medicine?

287
00:14:22,870 --> 00:14:24,330
Give me my medicine first.

288
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:26,150
Rong, you can't keep taking this medicine.

289
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:27,200
It's not good for your health.

290
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,730
I'm already not doing well!

291
00:14:30,030 --> 00:14:31,300
Rong, it's okay.

292
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:32,540
I'm back.

293
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:33,440
It's okay.

294
00:14:41,270 --> 00:14:41,870
Sit!

295
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:44,840
Jianren.

296
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:46,270
My head's already

297
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:47,080
